p in conjunction with auaf and an additional sixty six students currently are enrolled in the three legal studies courses offered in the spring of 2010 beginning in 2011 students who complete the full legal studies curriculum will receive a certificate in legal studies alep builds support for the program through site visits to afghanistan conferences and fundraising initiatives we host visiting professionals and hold symposia to improve the quality of the textbooks we produce alep has obtained generous support from public and private sources including a three year grant from inl at the state department website news & announcements law school's afghanistan legal education project wins state department grant and looks to expand september 28 2010 the stanford daily related erik jensen larry kramer afghanistan legal education project college lawyer in a land of few laws september 19 2010 the chronicle of higher education related erik jensen afghanistan legal education project rule of law program teaching law in afghanistan and other developing nations stanford law school makes legal education a global goal june 28 2010 stanford university news related erik jensen larry kramer afghanistan legal education project bhutan law and policy project rule of law program publications joseph a grundfest the united states securities and exchange commission v goldman sachs & co and fabrice tourre stanford calif rock center for corporate governance april 27 2010 recorded & past events march 2012 afghanistan legal education project's kabul trip presentation march 5 2012 from 12 45 pm 2 00 pm january 2012 law development and drugs in afghanistan january 31 2012 from 12 45 pm 2 00 pm join sls rule of law projects january 26 2012 from 12 45 pm 2 00 pm rule of law projects january 26 2012 from 12 45 pm 2 00 pm contact information stanford law school afghanistan legal education project morgan galland alep team leader 2010 2011 afghanistanlegaleducation gmail com related rule of law program 